reviewText: The story of Jim Vaus transformation.

I love the Billy Graham World Wide Pictures series of films."Wiretapper" is suppose to be based on a real man. A lovely film with a strong religious messge that never gets old. The entire family can watch this film. You do not have to take a shower after viewing this gem.

Made in 1955, an incredible true story of Jim Vaus. He was an electronics genius that got entangled with an organized crime syndicate.  His faith saves his life, Actual footage of the Billy Graham's 1949 LA Crusade. Needs to be re released on DVD. Stars Bill Williams, Georgia Lee, Douglas Kennedy, Richard Benedict, Stanley Clements, Paul Picerni, Ric Roman, Steve Conte, Art Gilmore
